The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases worldwide has surpassed 515 million, with over 6.2 million deaths, the latest data from Johns Hopkins University shows. Here is the latest: The Chinese mainland recorded 373 new confirmed COVID-19 cases on Wednesday, with 360 linked to local transmissions and 13 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Thursday. The U.S. State Department said on Wednesday that Secretary of State Antony Blinken tested positive for COVID-19 after attending the White House Correspondents' Dinner and related events over the weekend. The World Health Organization on Wednesday stressed the importance of testing and vaccinating, as two new Omicron sub-variants are driving an increase in reported COVID-19 cases in South Africa.